<div class="intro">
<div class="welcome">
Welcome to ECS, the School  of Electronics and Computer Science at the University of Southampton. ECS is one of the world's leading centres for 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050730084500/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/research/">research</a>, 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050730084500/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/about/teaching/">teaching</a>, <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050730084500/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/business/">enterprise and innovation</a> in Electronics, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science.
<div class="sig">Head of School: <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050730084500/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/people/wh">Professor Wendy Hall</a></div>
</div>
<div class="headline"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050730084500/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/767"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050730084500im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_767_img&amp;maxw=200&amp;maxh=150&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=b46ab3767f756a7ded55a0f7bb100344&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="" title="" border="0" width="200" height="133" class="thumbnail" /></a><h2 class="hide">Headline News</h2><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20050730084500/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/767">Network aims to advance memories for life</a></h3><p>As computers become capable of storing a lifetime's worth of memories and researchers explore prosthetic memories for humans, scientists at the University of Southampton have set up a network to develop a better understanding of how memory works and how it might be augmented by technological developments. One of the principal investigators is Professor Nigel Shadbolt from ECS.</p><p></p></div></div><div class='rightside'>

